{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"foregroundStyle","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"style","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ShapeStyle","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore10ShapeStyleP"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"style","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The color or pattern to use when filling in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"foreground elements. To indicate a specific value, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle\/image(_:sourceRect:scale:)"},{"type":"text","text":", or one of the gradient"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"types, like"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle\/linearGradient(colors:startPoint:endPoint:)"},{"type":"text","text":". To set a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"style that’s relative to the containing view’s style, use one of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"semantic styles, like "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/primary"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Return Value","level":2,"anchor":"return-value"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A view that uses the given foreground style.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this method to style"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"foreground content like text, shapes, and template images"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(including symbols):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["HStack {","    Image(systemName: \"triangle.fill\")","    Text(\"Hello, world!\")","    RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 5)","        .frame(width: 40, height: 20)","}",".foregroundStyle(.teal)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The example above creates a row of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/teal","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" foreground","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"elements:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use any style that conforms to the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"like the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/teal"},{"type":"text","text":" color in the example above, or the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"ShapeStyle\/linearGradient(colors:startPoint:endPoint:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" gradient"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shown below:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Text(\"Gradient Text\")","    .font(.largeTitle)","    .foregroundStyle(","        .linearGradient(","            colors: [.yellow, .blue],","            startPoint: .top,","            endPoint: .bottom","        )","    )"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Tip","style":"tip","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to fill a single ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Shape"},{"text":" instance with a style,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"use the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Shape\/fill(style:)"},{"text":" shape modifier instead because it’s more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"efficient.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OpenSwiftUI creates a context-dependent render for a given style."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example, a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" that you load from an asset catalog"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can have different light and dark appearances, while some styles"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"also vary by platform."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Hierarchical foreground styles like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle\/secondary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"don’t impose a style of their own, but instead modify other styles."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In particular, they modify the primary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"level of the current foreground style to the degree given by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the hierarchical style’s name."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To find the current foreground style to modify, OpenSwiftUI looks for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the innermost containing style that you apply with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"foregroundStyle(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" or the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/foregroundColor(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If you haven’t specified a style, OpenSwiftUI uses the default foreground"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"style, as in the following example:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["VStack(alignment: .leading) {","    Label(\"Primary\", systemImage: \"1.square.fill\")","    Label(\"Secondary\", systemImage: \"2.square.fill\")","        .foregroundStyle(.secondary)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you add a foreground style on the enclosing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", the hierarchical styling responds accordingly:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["VStack(alignment: .leading) {","    Label(\"Primary\", systemImage: \"1.square.fill\")","    Label(\"Secondary\", systemImage: \"2.square.fill\")","        .foregroundStyle(.secondary)","}",".foregroundStyle(.blue)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you apply a custom style to a view, the view disables the vibrancy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"effect for foreground elements in that view, or in any of its child"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"views, that it would otherwise gain from adding a background material"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"— for example, using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View\/background(_:ignoresSafeAreaEdges:)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifier. However, hierarchical styles applied to the default foreground"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"don’t disable vibrancy."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","remoteSource":{"fileName":"ForegroundStyleModifier.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Shape\/ShapeStyle\/ForegroundStyleModifier.swift#L112"},"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","modules":[{"relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"],"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"platforms":[{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"iOS","introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"10.15","unavailable":false},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"tvOS","introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"visionOS","introducedAt":"1.0","unavailable":false},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"watchOS","introducedAt":"6.0","unavailable":false}],"title":"foregroundStyle(_:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE15foregroundStyleyQrqd__AA05ShapeF0Rd__lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore5ImageV","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"foregroundStyle","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdent